body:
@markusweimer I've addressed your comments. It would be good to double check using the checkstyle though.

Yes, we're still in the stage of figuring out the best way to ship code/data to VortexWorkers. Let's discuss together on [the JIRA issue](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/REEF-504). I agree that we should be careful not to build any serious Vortex applications until this issue is resolved.

@bgchun I'm ready. Please go ahead and review it.

@afchung I've done a syntax pass, will do a logic one later. Overall feedback:
- Please add JavaDocs to all `public` classes, interfaces and members.
- Please add the `@DriverSide` / `@ClientSide` / `@TaskSide` annotations as well as the audience level annotations (`@Unstable`, `@Private`, ...)
